Sec. 301.053. ADVISORY COMMITTEES. The Texas Department of
Licensing and Regulation may establish advisory committees to advise
the Texas Department of Licensing and Regulation and to make
recommendations to the Texas Department of Licensing and Regulation
concerning legislation, policies, administration, research, and other
matters related to the duties, powers, or functions of the Texas
Department of Licensing and Regulation under this chapter.
Added by Acts 2003, 78th Leg., ch. 1276, Sec. 2.001(a), eff. Sept. 1,
2003.

